data.text:
After the success of the recently concluded La Nucía U-17 International Tournament, it is now time for women’s football in this town in Alicante. MFC has organised in collaboration with the City Council of La Nucia, the Norwegian Football Federation and Escape Travel, La Nucía Women’s U-19 International Tournament.

The event will see the participation of Norway, Italy, Sweden, Denmark, England, France, the Netherlands and Germany delighting the increasingly popular and well-followed women’s football.

The teams will face each other on 24th and 27th February at La Nucía Football Center, Meliá Villaitana Football Center and Estadi Olímpic Camilo Cano.

The scheduled matches are:

24/02

Norway U19 vs Italy U19 – 12:00H – La Nucía Football Center Field 1

Sweden U19 vs Denmark U19 – 14:00H – Meliá Villaitana Field 1

England U19 vs France U19 – 16:00H – La Nucía Football Center Field 1

Netherlands U19 vs Germany U19 – 19:00H – Estadi Olimpic Camilo Cano

27/02

Denmark U19 vs Netherlands U19 – 12:00H – La Nucía Football Center Field 1

Norway U19 vs England U19 – 14:00H – Meliá Villaitana Field 1

Germany U19 vs Italy U19 – 16:00H – La Nucía Football Center Field 1

France U19 vs Sweden U19- 19:00H – Estadi Olimpic Camilo Cano

This event is part of the project and the commitment to sports tourism of professional clubs in La Nucía, which with the new facilities “La Nucía Football Center”, will host in the coming months numerous professional teams and matches.

Marbella Football Center would like to thank the work of La Nucia Town Hall, the Norwegian Federation and Escape Travel for their professionalism, willingness and attention in the management of the event.
